Uses of Package
cornflakes.lang

  • Classes in cornflakes.lang used by cornflakes.lang 
    Class and Description
    F32Range
    The F32Range class is an iterable Range implementation used for defining a range between two floating-point values, including an optional increment size.
    FunctionalIterator
    The FunctionalIterator class is an iterator implementation which has several convenience functions commonly found in other languages.
    I32Range
    The I32Range class is an iterable Range implementation used for defining a range between two integer values, including an optional increment size.
    IteratorException
    An IteratorException is an unchecked exception thrown when an invalid operation is performed on a FunctionalIterator.
    Pointer
    The Pointer class is the superclass type for all Cornflakes pointer wrapper classes.
    Range
    The Range class represents any given range between two primitive values.
    Tuple
    The wrapper class for any Cornflakes tuple.
